text: The sieve-patterned moray eel (Gymnothorax cribroris) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the western Pacific Ocean and northern Australia. It was first named by Whitley in 1932 and is also commonly known as the sieve moray, brown- flecked reef eel, brown-flecked moray or the Australian moray. ==References== ==External links== * Fishes of Australia : Gymnothorax cribroris sieve- patterned moray eel Category:Marine fish of Northern Australia sieve-patterned moray eel
title: Sieve-patterned moray eel
